	(5,'information','GEPWNAGE LAN 7.0 ft. Deloitte',1,'en','<p>After our succesful sixth LAN last year, time is near for our seventh LAN. Like last year, Deloitte will join us! The most important information about the LAN is below. If you do not know what a LAN is, more information can be found by clicking ``What is a LAN?\'\' above.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>When:</strong> Fri March 13, 2015 @ 19:00h - Sun March 15 @ 16:00h (<small>times subject to changes</small>)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Official opening:</strong> <i>To be determined</i></li>\r\n <li><strong>Where:</strong> Het Klokgebouw (<small>Klokgebouw 50, Eindhoven</small>)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Costs:</strong> â‚¬ 20</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The LAN will be close to the same as last year: everybody is welcome on Friday from 19:00. Everyone will be provided with a table, a chair, 1 powersocket within 3 meters and 1 networkstocket within 5 meters. On Sunday, the LAN will stop at 16:00 and everyone has to go home before 17:00, or at least outside.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The LAN is meant for members of study association <a href=\"http://gewis.nl\">GEWIS</a> and employees of <a href=\"http://deloitte.nl\">Deloitte</a>.\r\n\r\n</p><h2>Deloitte Cyber Night</h2>\r\nDeloitte will attend with wonderful workshops and much more! Information about this will follow soon.\r\n\r\n<h2>Table, Chair, Power &amp; Network</h2>\r\n\r\n<p> There will be enough room for everyone to place their PC and a chair to sit in front of it. The tables will most likely be 120x60cm. At a maximum of 3 meters of each table there will be\r\na power plug for each person. If you want to plug in more electronics you\'d need to bring your own\r\npower strip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> There will be switches on the table to build a fast network. The distance from your PC/Laptop\r\nto a switch will be a maximum of 5 meters. It is unknown yet whether the network will be 100mbit\r\nor gigabit. There will also be an access point available for the internal network of the LAN. Both options provide internet connectivity. However please note that GEPWNAGE has the right to block certain services.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Sleeping Quarters</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This year it is not allowed to sleep on site, by regulations of the municipality. To solve this problem, we\'ve arranged a room with 34 (bunk)beds in the hotel nextdoor. Most likely this won\'t be enough. We would like to ask anyone living nearby to sleep at home, we can not guarantee a bed for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Signing up</h2>\r\n\r\n<p> Signing up can be done in two ways. The first is to write down your name, e-mail address, whether you\'re bringing a PC or a laptop, and whether you\'re a GEWIS member, Deloitte employee or neither at the <a href=\"http://gewis.nl/agenda/inschrijven.php?ID=748\">signup list</a> at GEWIS.\r\nThe second way is to compose an e-mail to lan(at)GEPWNAGE(dot)nl with the same information.\r\nIf we need to know something else about you, for example if you\'re a vegetarian or have an allergy, please let\r\nus know as well on the list or in your e-mail.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> After signing up one needs to pay participants money. You can do this by transfering the above\r\nmentioned amount  to giro account NL21 INGB 0005 7403 93 tnv PJA Bootsma en W Mouwen te Eindhoven.\r\nPlease mention your name and LAN 7.0 with this transfer. We can only guarantee a place for you if\r\nyour payment was received before Friday March 6th, 2015.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Stuff to take with you</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To enjoy the LAN nicely, do not forget to bring the following items:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>Laptop or PC including:<ul><li>Monitor</li><li>Keyboard</li><li>Mouse</li></ul></li>\r\n <li>Network cable (5 meter)</li>\r\n <li>Power strip (3 meter, if you have more than 1 plug)</li>\r\n <li>Headphones (seperate speakers will not be allowed!)</li>\r\n <li>Sleeping stuff</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYou are not allowed to bring your own drinks!','2015-02-15 18:45:23','2015-02-15 18:50:10',NULL),
	(6,'what-is-a-lan','What is a LAN?',0,'en','<p>Maybe you\'ve never been to a LAN-party because you think it is something for nerds.\r\nMaybe you\'ve never been there because you didn\'t know what to expect.\r\nBut you won\'t know what you\'re missing if you\'ve never been to one.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> The basic principle of a LAN is that everyone brings his or her PC (or laptop),\r\nsets it up at the LAN location, hooks it up to the network and starts playing games\r\nwith others over the network. There will be all opportunity to do this offcourse.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> But the LAN is a social gathering also. Something that can\'t be done through the network \r\nfor example is discussing a just finished good game while having a beer. Something that would\r\nalso be impossible through ethernet cables is watching a movie together when you feel like it,\r\nor just join each other for a good conversation (although, you\'ve got IRC, but still...).</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What do you do in that period?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>When the LAN opens you\'re welcome to bring in your PC/laptop to set up your station.\r\nAs soon as you boot up your system you can see which games are beeing played on the network.\r\nThere will also be a beamer on which we will display which servers are running so you won\'t need\r\nto try every game.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As soon as you don\'t feel like playing a game on your PC for a moment you can turn to the corner with\r\nconsoles to join in a game or cheer at people (or laugh at). You can also choose to take place at a \r\ntable with people to play a game of cards or have a chitchat for example.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> We\'ve also concidered your hunger and thirst. There will be candy and drinks in store supplied\r\nby the BAC which can be taken by using the well known \'afstreep\'list. There will also be bread etc.\r\nso you can make yourself some breakfast on saturday and sunday. There\r\nwill also be a meal on friday and saturday evening, so you won\'t have to starve.</p>','2015-02-15 18:46:25','2015-02-15 18:46:25',NULL),
